OL,3,CUnder-16s social media ban backed by
OL,4,CLords
OL,6,FThe Tory peer argued the evidence is
OL,7,F"overwhelming" for a ban, with support
OL,8,Franging from "medical professionals to
OL,9,Four police and national intelligence
OL,10,Fcommunity, from our teachers to
OL,11,Fhundreds of thousands of parents".
OL,13,FPeers voted 261 to 150, majority 111,
OL,14,Fin support of Lord Nash's amendment to
OL,15,Fthe Children's Wellbeing and Schools
OL,16,FBill on Wednesday.
OL,18,FSpeaking after the vote, Lord Nash
OL,19,Fsaid peers had "put our children's
OL,20,Ffuture first."
