OL,3,CUnder-16s social media ban backed by
OL,4,CLords
OL,6,F"This vote begins the process of
OL,7,Fstopping the catastrophic harm that
OL,8,Fsocial media is inflicting on a
OL,9,Fgeneration.
OL,11,F"Medical professionals, intelligence
OL,12,Fofficers, police officers, teachers
OL,13,Fand hundreds of thousands of parents
OL,14,Fclearly demanded action, and the Lords
OL,15,Fhave listened."
OL,17,FAustralia became the first country to
OL,18,Fban social media for under-16s in
OL,19,FDecember - a move brought in by the
OL,20,Fgovernment to make the internet a
OL,21,Fsafer place for young people.
