OL,3,CUnder-16s social media ban backed by
OL,4,CLords
OL,6,FWhile most schools already have some
OL,7,Fform of a ban on phones, many
OL,8,Fheadteachers have called for a
OL,9,Fstatutory one to make it easier for
OL,10,Fthem to enforce. They also argue it
OL,11,Fwould help to placate some parents who
OL,12,Fare unhappy about their child not
OL,13,Fhaving access to a phone at school.
OL,15,FWhile the guidance says schools must
OL,16,F"prohibit the use of mobile phones
OL,17,Fthroughout the school day", it makes
OL,18,Fclear "it is for school leaders to
OL,19,Fdevelop and implement a policy."
